<br>
Verant, you are effectivly killing your own expansion. You have to few things to do for the lower level players, as the monsters hit to hard/fast, the only used zones in SoV are basicly tower of frozen shadow and the great divide, with people farming Ry'Gor in the eastern wastes. Hardly anyone hunts in Skyshire or Kael anymore, and Velktor is usualy empty due to the low ZEM.<br>
But, you have basicly killed the &quot;high level game&quot;, or atleast a large portion of it.<br>
<br>
Not only did they nerf the dain, and he now poofs if you try and pull him (he poofed on about 5 different servers), they have BUFFED Lord Yelinak.<br>
<br>
Before the buff, and before Yelinak got /killed by the GMs, he was a very hard and challaneging fight unless you used an exploit (which is now fixed), ALOT of people died, and the fight was border-line annoying, but was balanced just enough that the fight could be considered fun.<br>
<br>
But, in Verants most resent patch, not only did players recieve a long list of nerfs, a few monsters got an INCREASE in power, ie: Yelinak. <br>
<br>
Yelniak, basicly tripple attacks for EVERY round of combat, allowing for SIX hits per melee round, his max hit is 600. That is 3600 melee-damage per round if he gets lucky. Some people did some number crunching last night, and on avg Yelinak was doing over 1k dmg per second, not even our warriors were living long enough to get healed if we had a direct aggro. <br>
<br>
With 52 people, having 12 clerics and a large ammount of warriors, Yelinak did not get below 50% health<br>
<br>
Having to deal with the nerfs in this patch is a learning curve enough, but then going off and buffing allready VERY difficult encounters? what the hell are you thinking verant.<br>
<br>
You are rather effectivly destroying the one remaning tactic that worked in this game - Aggro Control, and replacing it by the only option - Brute Force. You want epic mobs to take epic numbers to kill, but you game simply CAN NOT HANDLE IT.<br>
<br>
Please, before you design encounters that you want to see take &quot;50-100 deaths&quot; (as said by Narris), please design a game that can handle that many people in 1 area.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
